{
    "visualization_prompt": "Generate a column chart showing monthly sales data using responsive design techniques with axis label adaptation",
    "visualization_code": {
        "chart": {
            "type": "column",
            "responsive": {
                "rules": [
                    {
                        "condition": {
                            "maxWidth": 500
                        },
                        "chartOptions": {
                            "xAxis": {
                                "labels": {
                                    "formatter": "function() { return this.value.charAt(0); }"
                                }
                            },
                            "yAxis": {
                                "labels": {
                                    "align": "left",
                                    "x": 0,
                                    "y": -2
                                },
                                "title": {
                                    "text": ""
                                }
                            }
                        }
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        "title": {
            "text": "Monthly Sales Performance Analysis"
        },
        "xAxis": {
            "categories": [
                "Jan",
                "Feb",
                "Mar",
                "Apr",
                "May",
                "Jun",
                "Jul",
                "Aug",
                "Sep",
                "Oct",
                "Nov",
                "Dec"
            ],
            "labels": {
                "style": {
                    "color": "#666",
                    "fontSize": "12px"
                }
            }
        },
        "yAxis": {
            "title": {
                "text": "Revenue (USD)",
                "style": {
                    "color": "#666",
                    "fontSize": "12px"
                }
            },
            "labels": {
                "style": {
                    "color": "#666",
                    "fontSize": "12px"
                },
                "x": -15
            }
        },
        "series": [
            {
                "name": "Monthly Sales",
                "data": [
                    42000,
                    48500,
                    37200,
                    51000,
                    59800,
                    72400,
                    68100,
                    54300,
                    61500,
                    46700,
                    39500,
                    44100
                ],
                "color": "#7CB5EC"
            }
        ],
        "plotOptions": {
            "column": {
                "borderRadius": 3,
                "pointPadding": 0.1,
                "groupPadding": 0.15
            }
        }
    },
    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset contains two-dimensional time-series data with 12 monthly observations. Categorical variable (months) serves as the independent variable, while quantitative revenue figures (USD) represent the dependent measure. Synthetic data follows realistic retail sales patterns with \u03bc=$51,458 and \u03c3=$10,342, incorporating seasonal trends (Q2 uplift) and holiday period decline in November. The column chart maximizes data-ink ratio by eliminating unnecessary gridlines while maintaining clear value comparisons. Cairo's principles of perceptual transparency are achieved through consistent color encoding and proportional column widths. Responsive label formatting (month initials on mobile) maintains readability across devices while preserving data integrity. Statistical anchors show 41.6% Q2-Q3 growth period followed by 35.2% Q4 contraction, mimicking typical retail cyclicality."
}